This is a known breaking change. In .NET 10 (targeting Android API 35), **edge-to-edge** display is enforced and `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` (deprecated since API 30) no longer resizes the activity's content area.

The modern fix is to react to **window insets** so your layout adjusts its bottom padding when the IME (keyboard) appears.

### Solution

**1. Ensure `adjustResize` is still set** (it's needed but no longer sufficient alone):

In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`, keep:
```csharp
[Activity(WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustResize, ...)]
```

**2. Add an insets listener** in your `MainActivity`:

```csharp
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.ApplicationModel;

protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(Window!.DecorView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
}

private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

        // Use the larger of IME or nav-bar bottom inset
        int bottomPadding = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);

        v.SetPadding(v.PaddingLeft, v.PaddingTop, v.PaddingRight, bottomPadding);

        return insets;
    }
}
```

This listens for IME insets and pushes the entire content up by the keyboard's height.

### How it works

| .NET 9 (pre edge-to-edge) | .NET 10 (edge-to-edge) |
|---|---|
| System auto-resized the window | App draws behind system bars & keyboard |
| `AdjustResize` handled everything | You must read `WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime()` and apply padding yourself |

### Alternative: per-page approach

If you only need this on certain pages (e.g., your chat screen), you can set the padding on the specific MAUI view using a platform-specific handler instead of the `DecorView`, to avoid affecting other screens.
